# The custodian payload — one row per sealed secret.
#
# Format (pipe-separated, whitespace trimmed):
#   <sealed vault file>  |  <live deploy target>  |  <mode>  |  <kind>
#
# kind:
#   file       decrypt the sealed dotenv straight to the target path, chmod <mode>
#   wg-inject  decrypt to read WG_SERVER_PRIVATE_KEY, then render 05-wireguard/wg0.conf
#              (substituting the REPLACE_WITH_SERVER_PRIVATE_KEY placeholder) to target
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored. Targets containing ~ expand to
# the invoking user's home ON THE t630 (unseal runs there).
#
# vault file                  | deploy target             | mode | kind
vault/llm-router.env.sops     | ~/llm-router/.env         | 600  | file
vault/ttyd.env.sops           | /etc/a777ance/ttyd.env    | 600  | file
vault/pihole.env.sops         | ~/pihole/.env             | 600  | file
vault/wg0-key.env.sops        | /etc/wireguard/wg0.conf   | 600  | wg-inject
